## 5. Command + Data Review

### Legend
- ⭐⭐⭐ = High value  
- ⭐⭐ = Medium  
- ⭐ = Low  

---

### A. GitHub CLI (gh)

Reference: https://cli.github.com/manual/

| Command | What it Gets | Usefulness | Notes |
|--------|-------------|-----------|------|
| `gh repo list <org>` | repo inventory | ⭐⭐⭐ | strong baseline |
| `gh repo view <repo> --json` | repo metadata | ⭐⭐⭐ | structured JSON |
| `gh run list` | workflow runs | ⭐⭐⭐ | CI/CD visibility |
| `gh run view <id>` | workflow details | ⭐⭐ | requires multiple calls |
| `gh api /orgs/{org}/audit-log` | audit logs | ⭐⭐⭐ | governance + activity |
| `gh api /repos/{owner}/{repo}/actions/runs` | workflow data | ⭐⭐⭐ | deeper CI insight |

---

### B. Governance / Audit Data

Reference:  
https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-server@3.14/admin/monitoring-activity-in-your-enterprise  

| Area | Data | Usefulness | Notes |
|------|------|-----------|------|
| Audit logs | user/admin activity | ⭐⭐⭐ | key governance signal |
| Repo activity | commits/pushes | ⭐⭐ | partial coverage |
| Workflow usage | CI/CD runs | ⭐⭐⭐ | strong signal |

---

### C. ghe-governor (Admin Tooling)

Reference:  
https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/34220  

| Command Type | What it Shows | Usefulness | Notes |
|-------------|--------------|-----------|------|
| traffic (clone/fetch/push) | Git usage | ⭐⭐⭐ | strong for load analysis |
| concurrent clones | system stress | ⭐⭐⭐ | useful signal |
| CPU-heavy repos | performance issues | ⭐⭐⭐ | identifies bottlenecks |
| disk writes | storage usage | ⭐⭐ | situational |

---

### D. Less Useful / Limited Commands

Reference: https://cli.github.com/manual/

| Command | Why Limited | Usefulness |
|--------|------------|-----------|
| `gh repo clone` | not monitoring-related | ⭐ |
| `gh issue list` | product usage only | ⭐ |
| `gh pr list` | not infra-level | ⭐ |
| basic repo stats | lacks system context | ⭐⭐ |

