## 7. Key Findings

### 1. CLI is good for structured data
- Scriptable  
- Works across environments  
- Good for repo + workflow + audit data  

Reference: https://cli.github.com/manual/

---

### 2. CLI is not full monitoring
- Does not expose deep system metrics  

Reference:  
https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-server@3.16/admin/monitoring-and-managing-your-instance/monitoring-your-instance/about-the-monitor-dashboards  

---

### 3. Logs are critical
GitHub recommends:
- system logs  
- log forwarding  

Reference:  
https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-server@3.14/admin/monitoring-activity-in-your-enterprise/exploring-user-activity-in-your-enterprise/log-forwarding  

---

### 4. Built-in monitoring exists
- dashboards  
- health checks  

References:
- https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-server@3.16/admin/monitoring-and-managing-your-instance/monitoring-your-instance/about-the-monitor-dashboards  
- https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-server@3.14/admin/monitoring-and-managing-your-instance/monitoring-your-instance/generating-a-health-check-for-your-enterprise  

---

### 5. Best approach is hybrid
- CLI → structured data  
- Logs → observability  

---

## 8. Recommendation

Use a combined approach:

1. CLI for structured data  
2. Logs for system observability  
3. Export:
   - Splunk → logs  
   - Datadog → metrics  

Reference:  
https://docs.github.com/en/enterprise-server@3.14/admin/monitoring-activity-in-your-enterprise/exploring-user-activity-in-your-enterprise/log-forwarding  

